<Author>BenjaB
<Content>Good hotel in a fantastic city I stayed for a week at the NH Rallye, a 3-star hotel, while on a business trip. It is very close to Metro station Les Corts (about a 200 meter walk) which is on the L3 line, and if you've been to Barcelona you know that the Metro is the best way to get around. I had a very nice room with a large bathroom and a large desk to sit at while working on my laptop (via wireless connection). The breakfast buffet was good at 鈧?14.00 and the service was excellent. The bar next to the lobby was small but the service was also impeccable. Overall the hotel was not fancy, but for a business trip it was almost perfect -- almost, because the rate for the internet connection was appalling: 鈧?22.00 for 24 hours! Terrible. However, since everything else was outstanding I give it 4 stars. 
