<Author>FranciMilano
<Content>Very comfortable hotel For Christmas' Holidays my wife, my 5 years'old boy and I, decide to spend 5 days in Barcelona. We knew the Hotel Chain NH Hoteles (very popular in Spain) since we spent a very nice week during the New years eve 2006/2007 (Malaga and Sevilla).We've chosen the NH Rallye as it was the best price for ourselves (an average of 100鈧琾er room including taxes, services and a wonderful breakfast Buffet!).It's a three stars hotel, very close to the Barcelona Football Stadium, just 5 minutes walking from underground station (that reaches Plaza Catalunya in just 7-10 minutes!); the bus stop is located just one minute walking outside the main entrance.My room was very comfortable, clean, with a huge bathroom/shower. Safety box and minibar were already available in the room, as an LCD TV. The buffet breakfast was very nice and tastefull, with different kind of sweets, ham, eggs, sausages, fruits, yogurth, juices, biscuits, cakes etc. etc (it was perfect also for my son, which is not a gourmet!).To summarize: good choice, good price, staff very professional and always delicious. To recommend! 
