<Author>PollyB
<Content>Very good for what we wanted We were going to a concert at the Nou Camp (U2 - corking!), so booked this hotel because it is very close. As it was, we were in our room 20 minutes after the end of the concert, so it was just about perfect from that point of view.There was a mix up with our booking (the fault of the consolidator we booked through) which caused about half an hour's hassle, but once we were in, there were no problems. The room was a little on the small size (but I think we were given whatever was left because of the booking problem). However, there was a very large walk in shower and good facilities, view of Montjuc from our balcony, and it was surprisingly quiet given the location. Breakfast was also very good, and the terrace bar was nice.It wasn't the most central hotel, but only about 10 euros from Placa Catalunia in a taxi. Would definitely use again if we were going to the Nou Camp, but not for a more 'general' trip to Barca - we would stay somewhere more central. 
